# Troubleshooting TechNotes 

### Problem Description: create channel failed

#### background information
```go
2018-09-26 08:35:10.551 UTC [orderer/common/broadcast] Handle -> WARN 4a9 [channel: mychannel] Rejecting broadcast of message from 172.16.2.1:63380 with SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE: rejected by Consenter: will not enqueue, consenter for this channel hasn't started yet

```

#### Possible cause:
consenter not started or connect to a wrong consenter

#### solution:
set the correct consenter dns mapping in your peer yaml file


### Problem Description: join channel failed

#### background information
```go
2018-09-26 08:52:14.839 UTC [cauthdsl] deduplicate -> ERRO 668 Principal deserialization failure (MSP Org4MSP is unknown) for identity 
```
```go
2018-09-26 08:52:14.839 UTC [common/deliver] deliverBlocks -> WARN 675 [channel: mychannel] Client authorization revoked for deliver request from 172.16.2.1:64019: Failed to reach implicit threshold of 1 sub-policies, required 1 remaining: permission denied

```

#### Possible cause:
certificate or identity mistake or configtx.yaml Profiles does not contain the org
